<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>PM Skillshouse OCR Lab</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #f3f4f6;
      --card: #ffffff;
      --text: #1f2937;
      --muted: #6b7280;
      --border: #d1d5db;
      --accent: #f97316;
      --accent-soft: #fff7ed;
      --accent-border: #fdba74;
      --shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
      --radius: 18px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .wrap {
      max-width: 1120px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 28px 20px 60px;
    }

    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 46px;
      line-height: 1.05;
      color: #1f2937;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: 28px;
      color: #1f2937;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    .tag {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 7px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      border: 1px solid var(--accent-border);
      color: #9a3412;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 18px;
    }

    .mini {
      padding: 18px;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: #fafafa;
    }

    .mini strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 15px;
      color: #111827;
    }

    .upload-box {
      border: 2px dashed var(--accent-border);
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 22px;
    }

    .upload-box input[type="file"] {
      width: 100%;
      margin-top: 14px;
      padding: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #fff;
    }

    .actions {
      display: flex;
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 18px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    button {
      border: none;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 14px 18px;
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 700;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .btn-primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
    }

    .btn-secondary {
      background: #fff;
      color: #374151;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .status-box {
      margin-top: 18px;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: #f9fafb;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      color: #374151;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .draft-table-wrap {
      overflow-x: auto;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: #fff;
    }

    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      min-width: 860px;
    }

    th, td {
      padding: 14px 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: top;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    th {
      background: #f9fafb;
      color: #374151;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    td input, td select {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 10px 11px;
      border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
      border-radius: 10px;
      font-size: 14px;
      background: #fff;
    }

    .muted-note {
      margin-top: 12px;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #6b7280;
    }

    .warning-box {
      border: 1px solid #fde68a;
      background: #fffbeb;
      color: #92400e;
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      margin-top: 18px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card" style="text-align:center;">
      <img src="https://pmskillshouse.skillsbasedhub.co.za/logo.png" alt="PM Skillshouse Logo" style="height:70px; margin-bottom:12px;" />
      <div class="card">
      <div class="tag">SEPARATE OCR LAB</div>
      <h1>OCR Register Extraction Lab</h1>
      <p>
        This page is a separate prototype for scanned attendance register extraction.
        It is not yet linked to the live certificate workflow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>What this lab will do</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="mini">
          <strong>Phase 1 goal</strong>
          <p>Upload a scanned register and convert it into a draft editable table.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini">
          <strong>Human review step</strong>
          <p>Let the user correct unclear names, ID numbers, contact numbers, and emails before export.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini">
          <strong>Storage direction</strong>
          <p>Keep scans temporary, then delete after a retention period once review/export is complete.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini">
          <strong>Later integration</strong>
          <p>When stable, connect reviewed rows into the existing certificate and export flow.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Final Excel Export Structure</h2>
      <p>This OCR lab is being built around one final export format so both A3 and A4 extraction can feed the same output later.</p>
      <div class="draft-table-wrap" style="margin-top:16px;">
        <table style="min-width: 640px;">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Column Order</th>
              <th>Field Name</th>
              <th>Purpose</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>Row Number</td><td>Register row reference</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td>Name</td><td>Participant first/given name</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td>Surname</td><td>Participant surname/family name</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td>ID Number / DOB</td><td>Identity number or date of birth field</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td>Contact Number</td><td>Participant phone/contact number</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td>Email Address</td><td>Participant email address</td></tr>
            <tr><td>7</td><td>Gender</td><td>Detected or confirmed gender selection</td></tr>
            <tr><td>8</td><td>Employment Status</td><td>Employed / Unemployed</td></tr>
            <tr><td>9</td><td>Credit Report Required</td><td>Yes / No field</td></tr>
            <tr><td>10</td><td>Financial Advice Required</td><td>Yes / No field</td></tr>
            <tr><td>11</td><td>Match Confidence</td><td>System confidence for OCR/matching</td></tr>
            <tr><td>12</td><td>Review Status</td><td>Needs review / Reviewed</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="muted-note">
        Later, A3 extraction will populate the base list first, and A4 forms will enrich or confirm the same rows before final Excel export.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Upload scan or PDF</h2>
      <div class="upload-box">
        <p>Use this lab to test A3 and A4 register extraction without affecting the live prototype.</p>

        <div style="margin-top:18px;">
          <label style="font-weight:700; font-size:14px; color:#374151;">
            Register Type
          </label>
          <select id="registerType" style="width:100%; margin-top:8px; padding:12px; border:1px solid #d1d5db; border-radius:12px;">
            <option value="auto">Auto detect</option>
            <option value="liberty">Liberty Mind My Money Register</option>
            <option value="sanlam">Sanlam / Stokvel Register</option>
            <option value="template">Blank / Template Reference</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <input id="ocrFile" type="file" accept=".pdf,image/*" />
        <div class="actions">
          <button id="analyzeBtn" class="btn-primary" type="button">Start OCR Analysis</button>
          <button id="resetBtn" class="btn-secondary" type="button">Reset Lab</button>
        </div>
        <div id="ocrStatus" class="status-box">
          Waiting for a scanned file. This lab will aim to detect rows first, then enable review and correction.
        </div>
        <div class="warning-box">
          OCR output should be treated as a draft. Handwritten scans may contain unclear letters and digits, so users must be able to review and correct the extracted data before export.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Draft extracted rows</h2>
      <div class="draft-table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Row</th>
              <th>Name</th>
              <th>Surname</th>
              <th>ID Number / DOB</th>
              <th>Contact Number</th>
              <th>Email Address</th>
              <th>Gender</th>
              <th>Employment Status</th>
              <th>Credit Report Required</th>
              <th>Financial Advice Required</th>
              <th>Match Confidence</th>
              <th>Review Status</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="draftTableBody">
            <tr>
              <td>1</td>
              <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected name" /></td>
              <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected surname" /></td>
              <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected ID number or date of birth" /></td>
              <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected contact number" /></td>
              <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected email address" /></td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option value="">Unknown</option>
                  <option>Male</option>
                  <option>Female</option>
                </select>
              </td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option value="">Unknown</option>
                  <option>Employed</option>
                  <option>Unemployed</option>
                </select>
              </td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option value="">Unknown</option>
                  <option>Yes</option>
                  <option>No</option>
                </select>
              </td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option value="">Unknown</option>
                  <option>Yes</option>
                  <option>No</option>
                </select>
              </td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option>Unknown</option>
                  <option>High</option>
                  <option>Medium</option>
                  <option>Low</option>
                </select>
              </td>
              <td>
                <select>
                  <option>Needs review</option>
                  <option>Reviewed</option>
                </select>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="muted-note">
        This table now represents the intended final Excel structure. Later, A3 extraction will populate the participant list first, then A4 matching will enrich these rows before export.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    const ocrFile = document.getElementById("ocrFile");
    const analyzeBtn = document.getElementById("analyzeBtn");
    const resetBtn = document.getElementById("resetBtn");
    const ocrStatus = document.getElementById("ocrStatus");
    const draftTableBody = document.getElementById("draftTableBody");
    const registerTypeSelect = document.getElementById("registerType");

    function resetLab() {
      if (ocrFile) ocrFile.value = "";
      if (ocrStatus) {
        ocrStatus.textContent =
          "Waiting for a scanned file. This lab will aim to detect rows first, then enable review and correction.";
      }
      if (draftTableBody) {
        draftTableBody.innerHTML = `
          <tr>
            <td>1</td>
            <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected name" /></td>
            <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected surname" /></td>
            <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected ID number or date of birth" /></td>
            <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected contact number" /></td>
            <td><input value="" placeholder="Detected email address" /></td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option value="">Unknown</option>
                <option>Male</option>
                <option>Female</option>
              </select>
            </td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option value="">Unknown</option>
                <option>Employed</option>
                <option>Unemployed</option>
              </select>
            </td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option value="">Unknown</option>
                <option>Yes</option>
                <option>No</option>
              </select>
            </td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option value="">Unknown</option>
                <option>Yes</option>
                <option>No</option>
              </select>
            </td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option>Unknown</option>
                <option>High</option>
                <option>Medium</option>
                <option>Low</option>
              </select>
            </td>
            <td>
              <select>
                <option>Needs review</option>
                <option>Reviewed</option>
              </select>
            </td>
          </tr>
        `;
      }
    }

    function startAnalysis() {
      if (!ocrFile || !ocrFile.files || !ocrFile.files[0]) {
        ocrStatus.textContent = "Please choose a scanned file or PDF first.";
        return;
      }

      const file = ocrFile.files[0];
      const selectedType = registerTypeSelect ? registerTypeSelect.value : "auto";
      ocrStatus.textContent =
        "File loaded (" + file.name + "). Register type: " + selectedType +
        ". Next step: detect rows and extract draft data for review.";
    }

    analyzeBtn.addEventListener("click", startAnalysis);
    resetBtn.addEventListener("click", resetLab);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
